00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:04.996
- The guy at Fatburger just shook his head.
- Okay. it doesn't matter. Doesn't matter.

232
00:11:04.997 --> 00:11:07.999
The point of this dinner is for you
and Marcus to get on the same page.

233
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:11.002
Don't worry. We're going to be on
the same page. Oh. here he comes.

234
00:11:11.003 --> 00:11:13.213
Marcus. thank you so much for coming.

235
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:14.214
Sorry. I'm late.

236
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:17.676
I had dinner at home.
My chef does coq au vin Tuesday.

237
00:11:17.677 --> 00:11:19.177
You both had dinner?

238
00:11:19.178 --> 00:11:22.681
I literally preordered
three large format platters.

239
00:11:22.682 --> 00:11:24.683
- I'll take mine to go.
- You know what? Whatever.

240
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.935
You're here now. That's all that matters.

241
00:11:26.936 --> 00:11:28.853
Guys. I'm so happy we're doing this.

242
00:11:28.854 --> 00:11:32.357
so we can clear the air
and have a great season. right?

243
00:11:32.358 --> 00:11:35.151
Oh. we were having a great season
when I was getting the ball.

244
00:11:35.152 --> 00:11:36.653
Yeah. well. it… it's a long season.

245
00:11:36.654 --> 00:11:40.199
Hey. Norm. let's tell Marcus
what a great value he is to the team.

246
00:11:42.368 --> 00:11:43.618
Okay. look. Marcus. I get it.

247
00:11:43.619 --> 00:11:47.080
You've hit some pretty big shots
for your team whenever they needed it.

248
00:11:47.081 --> 00:11:47.997
Exactly.

249
00:11:47.998 --> 00:11:50.876
And you're still the big dog
in the locker room. I know that.

250
00:11:51.377 --> 00:11:53.712
- But this is about championships…
- Oh.

251
00:11:53.713 --> 00:11:57.132
…and when you don't run the play I call.
you kinda screw up my whole goddamn plan.

252
00:11:57.133 --> 00:11:58.591
Oh. you got a plan?

253
00:11:58.592 --> 00:12:00.802
Yeah. that's right.
And you gotta get on board with it.

254
00:12:00.803 --> 00:12:05.057
I knew you were trying to cut me out.
This is on you. I'm out of here.

255
00:12:05.641 --> 00:12:08.436
- Chef Greg made profiteroles.
- Marcus!

256
00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:11.688
Norm. what was that?

257
00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:13.481
You're supposed to get him to like you.

258
00:12:13.482 --> 00:12:16.109
I'm sorry. I blew it.
I was trying to do a tough love thing.

259
00:12:16.110 --> 00:12:18.862
I saw a TED Talk about boundaries.
Didn't watch the whole thing.

260
00:12:18.863 --> 00:12:21.906
<i>- Survivor</i> was coming on.
- Okay. well. it didn't work. did it?

261
00:12:21.907 --> 00:12:25.243
And it made him madder than he was
minutes ago. and now I'm mad.

262
00:12:25.244 --> 00:12:26.161
Look. I can fix this.

263
00:12:26.162 --> 00:12:28.329
- How?
- We got the big road trip coming up.

264
00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:31.708
That's when teams bond. okay?
There's no family. no distractions.

265
00:12:31.709 --> 00:12:33.293
I'll pack the travel <i>Scrabble.</i>

266
00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:35.795
Before you know it.
it's all gonna be copacetic.

267
00:12:35.796 --> 00:12:38.174
Which is a hell of a <i>Scrabble</i> word.

268
00:12:38.799 --> 00:12:41.176
- You can just box all that up.
- I don't eat pork. though.

269
00:12:41.177 --> 00:12:43.136
What? There not one thing
of pork on there.

270
00:12:43.137 --> 00:12:45.472
- That's not pork? What is that?
- It's a seafood tower.

271
00:12:45.473 --> 00:12:47.557
Oh. uh... Oh. Uh. bring it back.

272
00:12:49.018 --> 00:12:51.227
{\an8}<i>The nightmare road trip
comes to an end</i>

273
00:12:51.228 --> 00:12:53.189
{\an8}<i>as the Waves get blown out in Miami.</i>

274
00:12:53.773 --> 00:12:56.024
Marcus. you guys went 0-6
on the road trip.

275
00:12:56.025 --> 00:12:58.526
{\an8}Why did Coach Stinson leave you
on the bench in the fourth?

276
00:12:58.527 --> 00:13:01.070
{\an8}You'd have to ask him. I'm not the coach.

277
00:13:01.071 --> 00:13:03.323
{\an8}I'm just
the franchise's all-time leading scorer.

278
00:13:03.324 --> 00:13:05.950
{\an8}Did you go to the locker room
early to prove a point?

279
00:13:05.951 --> 00:13:07.036
<i>I had a headache.</i>

280
00:13:07.536 --> 00:13:09.662
Okay. I'm gonna say this
as kindly as I know how.

281
00:13:09.663 --> 00:13:12.749
Norm is a fucking loser.

282
00:13:12.750 --> 00:13:13.750
He sucks.

283
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:15.960
He's an anchor around our necks.
He's dead weight.

284
00:13:15.961 --> 00:13:18.505
And I want to say "I told you so."
but I'm a good guy.

285
00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:20.298
The season just started.

286
00:13:20.299 --> 00:13:22.884
I get it. It looks bad.
and you're gonna take a bit of an L.

287
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:25.470
We… we'll take a bit of an L
if we let him go.

288
00:13:25.471 --> 00:13:27.138
but Jesus. we're fucking 3-12.

289
00:13:27.139 --> 00:13:30.600
We're supposed to be contenders
for the championship. not the lottery.

290
00:13:30.601 --> 00:13:32.644
Isla. they're right. okay?
I mean. this is bad.

291
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:34.104
At this rate. we're gonna end up…

292
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.065
Wait a second here.

293
00:13:37.066 --> 00:13:39.192
- Carry the one…
- Okay. he's gonna be a while.

294
00:13:39.193 --> 00:13:41.486
Look. we gotta do this now
so we can salvage the season.

295
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:43.154
No. I hired Norm for a reason.

296
00:13:43.155 --> 00:13:44.447
I know he can do this.

297
00:13:44.448 --> 00:13:46.616
And if Ali was here.
she'd agree with me too.

298
00:13:46.617 --> 00:13:48.201
Well. thank God she's gone.

299
00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:51.997
Look. you're wrong. Just fucking admit it.
Even Dad would admit when he was wrong.

300
00:13:56.836 --> 00:13:58.419
You know what. Cam? You're right.

301
00:14:00.881 --> 00:14:03.675
Ha! 62 and 20.

302
00:14:03.676 --> 00:14:06.303
- That… that's actually not that bad.
- No. you did it backwards.

303
00:14:06.887 --> 00:14:08.806
And somehow upside down too.

304
00:14:09.682 --> 00:14:11.766
Hey. thanks for coming in. Norm.

305
00:14:11.767 --> 00:14:15.436
Yeah. don't worry. I know why I'm here.
I blew it. right? I blew it with Marcus.

306
00:14:15.437 --> 00:14:16.354
Norm.

307
00:14:16.355 --> 00:14:18.606
The guy doesn't respect me.
and we're on a losing streak.

308
00:14:18.607 --> 00:14:19.649
- Norm.
- You gotta fire me.

309
00:14:19.650 --> 00:14:22.318
Norm. stop talking
and let me say something.

310
00:14:22.319 --> 00:14:24.321
- Just sit.
- Okay.

311
00:14:25.489 --> 00:14:26.906
Okay. yes.

312
00:14:26.907 --> 00:14:30.702
There are a lot of people
that would like to see you get fired.

313
00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.079
but that's not happening today.

314
00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:33.872
Okay.

315
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:35.373
Do you remember my mom?

316
00:14:35.374 --> 00:14:37.041
Yeah. yeah. proud. beautiful woman.

317
00:14:37.042 --> 00:14:39.294
Didn't need the second facelift.
if you ask me.

318
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.546
but. uh. she and your dad.
they were a great couple.

319
00:14:41.547 --> 00:14:44.591
My dad cheated on her
like 500 million times.

320
00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:45.758
- Yes. he did.
- Yeah.

321
00:14:45.759 --> 00:14:48.761
But despite my dad's mistakes.
he loved my mom

322
00:14:48.762 --> 00:14:52.390
and he did whatever he could
to keep the family together.

323
00:14:52.391 --> 00:14:54.935
And so when my mom started to feel
really neglected.

324
00:14:55.644 --> 00:14:59.397
he'd do whatever he could to make her
feel like she was his number one girl.

325
00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:04.027
And I am talking diamonds.
a convertible. a house in Palm Springs.

326
00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:05.863
Do you see what I'm getting at here?

327
00:15:06.488 --> 00:15:10.783
You want me to buy Marcus a car. Isla?
I mean. I'm underwater on my condo.

328
00:15:10.784 --> 00:15:13.787
No. Norm. Norm. I want you to make Marcus
feel like your number one girl.

329
00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:16.999
Uh…

330
00:15:17.499 --> 00:15:18.458
I get it.

331
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:19.793
Hmm. Okay.

332
00:15:20.377 --> 00:15:22.587
But whatever happens.
don't tell him about that analogy.

333
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:24.631
because he'll just fixate on
being the woman.

334
00:15:24.632 --> 00:15:25.591
I get it.

335
00:15:26.216 --> 00:15:29.678
<i>Halftime in LA.
Marcus Winfield leads all scorers with 18.</i>

336
00:15:30.262 --> 00:15:32.597
Best we've looked in weeks.
and we're still losing.

337
00:15:32.598 --> 00:15:34.849
Well. at least Norm's
getting Marcus the ball.

338
00:15:34.850 --> 00:15:38.937
Isla. Al Fleischman. aka The Flush Man.
Toilet King of Orange County.

339
00:15:38.938 --> 00:15:41.356
Yeah. Hey. Al. how are you?

340
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:44.943
Oh. good. good. good.
Now that I am front row. center court.

341
00:15:47.112 --> 00:15:48.279
Yeah. did Ali do that?

342
00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:49.614
No. Ali was a waste of time.

343
00:15:49.615 --> 00:15:51.824
I think she wanted to hook up with me.
I don't know.

344
00:15:51.825 --> 00:15:53.827
Cam made it happen. He's my boy now.

345
00:15:54.453 --> 00:15:56.704
Ness. Ness. why don't you go get him
some swag?

346
00:15:56.705 --> 00:15:58.624
Yeah. Oh. you know what?

347
00:15:59.249 --> 00:16:03.127
We have a sweatshirt. no sleeves.
covered in sequins. Screams your name.

348
00:16:03.128 --> 00:16:04.629
- Oh my God.
- Yeah.

349
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:05.964
I feel seen. man.

350
00:16:05.965 --> 00:16:07.215
Yes. I see you.

351
00:16:10.010 --> 00:16:11.511
<i>Winfield brings it up.</i>

352
00:16:11.512 --> 00:16:13.304
<i>He's having his best game of the season.</i>

353
00:16:13.305 --> 00:16:15.556
<i>Coach's been calling
his number all night.</i>

354
00:16:15.557 --> 00:16:17.016
<i>and Marcus has been responding.</i>

355
00:16:18.018 --> 00:16:18.977
Charge!

356
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:21.062
<i>Oh. but he's called
for the charge.</i>

357
00:16:21.063 --> 00:16:22.814
- That's on me?
- Two-two blue.

358
00:16:22.815 --> 00:16:25.191
You gotta be kidding me. ref.
That's terrible.

359
00:16:25.192 --> 00:16:26.275
Going this way.

360
00:16:26.276 --> 00:16:28.486
- I'm serious. Marcus.
- Call those feet set?

361
00:16:28.487 --> 00:16:30.488
- Give me the ball. I'm not kidding.
- Hell no.

362
00:16:30.489 --> 00:16:32.824
- Give me the ball. or I'm gonna T you up.
- Back off. Marcus.

363
00:16:32.825 --> 00:16:34.742
- Give me the ball!
- Back off. Marcus. Back off.

364
00:16:34.743 --> 00:16:36.703
My man. what the hell was that?

365
00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:37.870
That's not a charge!

366
00:16:37.871 --> 00:16:39.872
You got bird shit in your eye?

367
00:16:39.873 --> 00:16:43.126
I get that you're the worst ref
in the league. but seriously.

368
00:16:43.127 --> 00:16:44.752
How can you make that call?

369
00:16:44.753 --> 00:16:46.879
- That's a tech.
- I don't give a shit about a tech.

370
00:16:46.880 --> 00:16:49.007
You can't make that call
on Marcus Winfield.

371
00:16:49.008 --> 00:16:51.300
You're just lucky
you get to watch him play.

372
00:16:51.301 --> 00:16:53.177
Oh. wait. I forgot you're blind.

373
00:16:53.178 --> 00:16:55.681
You put some respect on his name.
you dumb bastard.

374
00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:57.223
That's it!

375
00:16:57.224 --> 00:16:58.474
You're out of here.

376
00:16:58.475 --> 00:17:01.102
Good 'cause I can't stand
to watch you work.

377
00:17:01.103 --> 00:17:02.563
You dumb asshole. Give me that.

378
00:17:05.774 --> 00:17:07.734
Oh. no. no. don't touch.
It's my knee. yeah.

379
00:17:07.735 --> 00:17:10.195
Oh. shit. that's the good one too.

380
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:12.864
Medic! We need a doc here.

381
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:19.704
Hey. man. you knocked over my açai bowl.

382
00:17:19.705 --> 00:17:20.788
Wait. What the hell?

383
00:17:20.789 --> 00:17:22.665
Charlie. what is going on?

384
00:17:22.666 --> 00:17:24.584
- We said no more shooting here.
- Let me explain.

385
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:26.794
Hold on. If you're gonna talk.
we'll need to mic you.

386
00:17:26.795 --> 00:17:28.087
No. no. Do not come near me.

387
00:17:28.088 --> 00:17:30.131
Look. I told the producers
we couldn't shoot here.

388
00:17:30.132 --> 00:17:32.842
but they loved our drama so much.
they just wanted to get a bit more.

389
00:17:32.843 --> 00:17:34.802
So tell me to kick everybody out
and be mad.

390
00:17:34.803 --> 00:17:37.221
No. I am mad. okay?
And I'm not part of this show.

391
00:17:37.222 --> 00:17:39.015
- All right. we'll boom in.
- Do not… Stop it.

392
00:17:39.016 --> 00:17:41.517
I don't want to be a part of…
Oh. fuck off!

393
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:42.435
Come here.

394
00:17:42.436 --> 00:17:44.270
Keep rolling.
We'll count slate it at the end.

395
00:17:44.271 --> 00:17:46.355
Which one of you filmed my butt? Huh?

396
00:17:46.356 --> 00:17:47.191
Oh. shit.

397
00:17:47.775 --> 00:17:48.900
Can you excuse us. please?

398
00:17:48.901 --> 00:17:51.194
First. they told us
to go into the living room.

399
00:17:51.195 --> 00:17:52.445
Then they put us in here.

400
00:17:52.446 --> 00:17:54.530
- Where do you want us to set up?
- I don't care.

401
00:17:54.531 --> 00:17:56.574
Anywhere but my bedroom would be great.
Thank you.

402
00:17:56.575 --> 00:17:59.577
Sandy. I know that you're mad. all right?
But we are catching on.

403
00:17:59.578 --> 00:18:02.955
People loved seeing your ass. Jon Hamm
played it on <i>Watch What Happens.</i>

404
00:18:02.956 --> 00:18:05.416
So your plan was
to have a fight on camera?

405
00:18:05.417 --> 00:18:06.459
Have you gone insane?

406
00:18:06.460 --> 00:18:07.710
This is how we make it.

407
00:18:07.711 --> 00:18:10.254
If this plays out.
we could… we could get our own show.

408
00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:12.381
I was thinking
we could call it <i>Groom Mates.</i>

409
00:18:12.382 --> 00:18:15.593
- It could be about us opening a dog salon.
- I have a job.

410
00:18:15.594 --> 00:18:18.930
And I thought you wanted to be an actor.
not a reality star.

411
00:18:18.931 --> 00:18:21.432
Come on. every actor wants to be
a reality star now. all right.

412
00:18:21.433 --> 00:18:23.309
If this works. we could get on <i>Traitors</i>.

413
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:24.228
No. I don't…

414
00:18:25.521 --> 00:18:27.814
No. still no.
I would be very good on that show

415
00:18:27.815 --> 00:18:29.899
and I would win.
but that's not what I signed up for.

416
00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:33.570
Well. this is what I want. all right?
And I'm not… I'm not giving it up.

417
00:18:35.656 --> 00:18:39.076
So you would rather be on TV
than be with me?

418
00:18:39.660 --> 00:18:41.245
That… Sandy…

419
00:18:42.913 --> 00:18:46.834
No. look. all I know is I don't want to be
with someone who'd make me choose.

420
00:18:51.505 --> 00:18:53.339
Then I guess we want different things.

421
00:18:54.716 --> 00:18:56.009
Wow. I guess we do.

422
00:19:00.764 --> 00:19:01.723
So this is it?

423
00:19:03.892 --> 00:19:05.227
Yeah. I think so.

424
00:19:14.528 --> 00:19:15.987
- Hey. Charlie.
- Yeah?

425
00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:18.198
- They need you.
- Okay.

426
00:19:19.324 --> 00:19:20.576
Goodbye. Sandy.

427
00:19:24.413 --> 00:19:27.957
Hey. man.
there's a baked potato bar at crafty.

428
00:19:29.543 --> 00:19:30.419
Thank you.

429
00:19:35.340 --> 00:19:37.675
Hey. how you doing. Norm?

430
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:41.304
I'm in a little pain.
but. uh. I think it's all superficial. so…

431
00:19:41.305 --> 00:19:43.431
No. that ligament is gone. dog.

432
00:19:43.432 --> 00:19:46.225
Look. his shin is just floating in blood
right now.

433
00:19:46.226 --> 00:19:48.227
- It's… it's crazy.
- Oh. Son of a bitch.

434
00:19:48.228 --> 00:19:50.062
Please. tell me that we won. at least.

435
00:19:50.063 --> 00:19:51.230
- By 15.
- Good.

436
00:19:51.231 --> 00:19:52.982
I mean. you went psycho out there.

437
00:19:52.983 --> 00:19:56.944
And I know in today's world it's not cool
when a white guy just totally loses it.

438
00:19:56.945 --> 00:19:58.154
but it was awesome.

439
00:19:58.155 --> 00:20:00.156
So I could do that again.
I could… I got rage.

440
00:20:00.157 --> 00:20:02.825
I was born with one testicle.
I hate the world.

441
00:20:02.826 --> 00:20:03.868
Oh. yeah. No. no. no.

442
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:07.121
It's fine. but Marcus did have
his best game of the season.

443
00:20:07.122 --> 00:20:09.583
and I think it had a lot to do
with your performance.

444
00:20:10.209 --> 00:20:15.379
Well. I just… had to let him know
that he's my best girl.

445
00:20:18.383 --> 00:20:19.760
Yeah.

446
00:20:21.094 --> 00:20:22.678
Yeah. you need your best girl.

447
00:20:22.679 --> 00:20:23.804
Yeah.

448
00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:26.224
I gotta go.

449
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:28.142
- Um. rest up. Norm.
- All right.

450
00:20:28.143 --> 00:20:29.477
Marcus. hey.

451
00:20:29.478 --> 00:20:32.188
I don't know if you heard.
but my son's Bar Mitzvah is approaching.

452
00:20:32.189 --> 00:20:36.234
and I was hoping you could sign.
like. 300 yarmulkes by Saturday.

453
00:20:36.235 --> 00:20:37.902
Hey. Doc. let me get you real quick.

454
00:20:37.903 --> 00:20:40.864
- I'll just forge 'em. It's fine.
- Oh. we'll… we'll see if he's available.

455
00:20:43.450 --> 00:20:47.703
- You know the ref made the right call?
- Oh yeah. That was a charge big time.

456
00:20:51.208 --> 00:20:53.043
Thanks for having my back out there.

457
00:20:54.586 --> 00:20:58.965
Marcus. look. you're the best player
that I've ever had the honor of coaching.

458
00:20:58.966 --> 00:21:02.093
but I gotta get these young guys ready
for when the playoffs come

459
00:21:02.094 --> 00:21:03.845
so they have your back.

460
00:21:04.763 --> 00:21:06.598
Even Marcus Winfield can't win alone.

461
00:21:07.516 --> 00:21:09.518
Well. it'd be close. but…

462
00:21:12.104 --> 00:21:13.063
I'm with you. Coach.

463
00:21:14.106 --> 00:21:15.940
I'm with you. Marcus. Yeah.

464
00:21:15.941 --> 00:21:18.859
- Hold on. hold on. One favor. please.
- Hmm?

465
00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:20.027
Carry me to the toilet.

466
00:21:20.028 --> 00:21:22.196
- It's right around there.
- Yeah.

467
00:21:22.197 --> 00:21:25.241
Just drop me off
and then come back in 20 minutes.

468
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:29.120
<i>And that'll do it
from Ally Bank Arena.</i>

469
00:21:29.121 --> 00:21:32.206
<i>LA cruises to an easy win. 104-89.</i>

470
00:21:32.207 --> 00:21:33.499
Fuck that.

471
00:21:33.500 --> 00:21:35.876
- Damn it.
- Why… Why are you mad? They won.

472
00:21:35.877 --> 00:21:38.422
I'm not mad. I'm not even acting mad.
I just…

473
00:21:39.172 --> 00:21:40.131
It's complicated.

474
00:21:41.258 --> 00:21:43.592
- Here.
- Uh. actually. I'm good.

475
00:21:43.593 --> 00:21:47.054
It's my mom's birthday tomorrow.
and I promised I'd take her to brunch.

476
00:21:47.055 --> 00:21:48.931
Oh. come on. It's like a cup of coffee.

477
00:21:50.183 --> 00:21:51.892
- Come on.
- Okay. okay. okay.

478
00:21:57.107 --> 00:21:59.776
Ali. Ali!

479
00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:02.570
Where the hell is Ali Lee?

480
00:22:02.571 --> 00:22:04.447
We are looking to diversify
our sponsorships.

481
00:22:04.448 --> 00:22:08.326
and we think your caribou jerky is exactly
the type of jerky we've been missing.

482
00:22:08.327 --> 00:22:09.161
Ali.

483
00:22:10.203 --> 00:22:11.120
Ali.

484
00:22:11.121 --> 00:22:12.538
Oh!

485
00:22:12.539 --> 00:22:14.081
Oh! Uh.

486
00:22:14.082 --> 00:22:17.501
Oh my God. Wait. Isla.
what are you doing here? Are you okay?

487
00:22:17.502 --> 00:22:18.836
I… I'm here for you.

488
00:22:18.837 --> 00:22:20.963
Isla Gordon. I know
you're not interrupting a meeting

489
00:22:20.964 --> 00:22:23.132
with two of our most important sponsors.

490
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:25.217
Ali. I've been a fucking horrible friend.

491
00:22:25.218 --> 00:22:28.054
and I'm not fucking leaving here
unless it's with you.

492
00:22:28.055 --> 00:22:30.765
and nothing will make me
fucking change my mind.

493
00:22:30.766 --> 00:22:32.641
Hey. use your church words.

494
00:22:32.642 --> 00:22:35.102
- Uh. th… they don't really swear in here.
- This is outrageous.

495
00:22:35.103 --> 00:22:38.356
Wayne. Lief. I am so sorry
for this disgusting display.

496
00:22:38.357 --> 00:22:39.690
Oh. shut up. Magnus.

497
00:22:39.691 --> 00:22:42.027
You know. you have a mouth
like a Saskatoon lumberjack.

498
00:22:43.236 --> 00:22:45.155
Ali. I should've treated you better.

499
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:49.116
Anything I do without you
just feels wrong.

500
00:22:49.117 --> 00:22:52.745
Also. when my brothers say something dumb.
I have no one to roll my eyes with.

501
00:22:52.746 --> 00:22:54.164
and I love you like a sister.

502
00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:56.874
I mean. probably more than a sister.

503
00:22:56.875 --> 00:23:00.920
because if I… if I had one.
she'd be a big bitch.

504
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:04.131
I can't believe you came up here.

505
00:23:04.132 --> 00:23:06.926
especially with the weather grounding
all small aircraft. I'm…

506
00:23:08.553 --> 00:23:10.388
Did you fly commercial?

507
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:13.182
First class.
but they sat me near the bathroom.

508
00:23:13.183 --> 00:23:14.476
and it smelled awful.

509
00:23:15.560 --> 00:23:18.146
Ali. if you come back to LA.

510
00:23:18.897 --> 00:23:21.899
I will kick Cam out of your office.
and you can redecorate it.

511
00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:24.193
I still won't use any of
your shitty high school friends.

512
00:23:24.194 --> 00:23:26.445
Of course not. They all suck.

513
00:23:27.614 --> 00:23:28.948
I missed you.

514
00:23:31.034 --> 00:23:34.788
Magnus. I say this
with absolutely zero respect.

515
00:23:35.372 --> 00:23:37.123
I quit. Let's go. Let's get out of here.

516
00:23:37.124 --> 00:23:40.084
You're making a huge mistake
that I… that I won't ever forgive.

517
00:23:40.085 --> 00:23:43.504
Now. someone help pack up Ali's things
and get 'em a car service to the airport.

518
00:23:43.505 --> 00:23:45.714
Oh God. thank you for saving me
from this shithole.

519
00:23:45.715 --> 00:23:47.174
I missed you so much.

520
00:23:47.175 --> 00:23:49.635
And I'm not getting married
without my maid of honor.

521
00:23:49.636 --> 00:23:53.140
Oh. that's right. Big week. Your wedding.
Boston's coming into town.

522
00:23:53.640 --> 00:23:54.557
Right.

523
00:23:54.558 --> 00:23:55.558
Boston.
